title: BREAKING: Emergency crews scrambled as plane crash lands at major airport
text:
CRASH: It is not yet clear whether anyone is injured 
Emergency services are scrambling to Essendon Airport after the plane reportedly crashed into a building. 
Dramatic eyewitness pictures show thick black smoke billowing from the runway. 
It is understood the plane crashed at around 9am, with reports of explosions shortly after. 
One shocked passerby told told 3AW: "There is constant explosions going off, there is black smoke billowing into the sky." 
TWITTER SMOKING: The plane reportedly crashed into a building #BREAKING : An Air Ambulance has crashed into the DFO factory outlet near Essendon Airport in Melbourne. #TMS7 pic.twitter.com/uLJuGUumKu â€” The Morning Show (@morningshowon7) February 20, 2017 
It is not yet clear whether there were any casualties. 
Police are currently evacuating the area.
